com.github.games647.scoreboardstats

Class FastOfflinePlayer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.games647.scoreboardstats.FastOfflinePlayer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationSerializable, AnimalTamer, OfflinePlayer, ServerOperator

    public class FastOfflinePlayer
extends Object
implements OfflinePlayer
    Since 1.7 Bukkit introduced CraftServer.getOfflinePlayer(String name). This method is blocking as it looks up the cache. So it could cause lags on big servers. Because we only need the name this class is made. Bukkit already implemented methods to get around this problem, but the scoreboard team isn't yet modified for methods, which can be called just with a string. Servers below 1.7 with use of this class doesn't need to search for the player.
    See Also:
    Bukkit.getOfflinePlayer(java.lang.String)
